# Terminal Commands

## Virtual Environment Usage
When running any Python commands in terminal, always activate the virtual environment first:

### Template
```bash
source venv/bin/activate && [python-command]
```

### Examples
```bash
# Running tests
source venv/bin/activate && python -m pytest tests/test_categories_service.py -v

# Running Python scripts  
source venv/bin/activate && python -m scripts.firestore_cli

# Installing packages
source venv/bin/activate && pip install package-name
```

### Rationale
- Ensures consistent Python environment and dependencies
- Prevents issues with system Python vs project Python
- Maintains isolation from global Python packages
